aa63bc6d-d9ae-40f1-956a-8fdac9279294.3e751dfe-ab23-4635-9461-98219a22ea8b.description=
This workflow creates the MOE topology of server groups and servers in CSA. It adds the infrastructure service child components - server groups and servers created by MOE, adds relevant public actions and resource bindings to these components.

Inputs\:

RSC_PROVIDER_ID	- CSA Resource Provider Id for the MOE provider
svcInstanceId	- CSA Service Instance Id
ioXml		- Output XML returned by the MOE Add Server or Create Service API calls
infraComponentId	- CSA Service Component Id of the Infrastructure component
userIdentifier	- CSA User Identifier
serviceName		- MOE Service Name created

Responses\:
success - Workflow completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State aa63bc6d-d9ae-40f1-956a-8fdac9279294.c081a188-576a-4f75-9820-8cd592bf44ec.description=
This subflow was created by the Web Services Wizard to invoke the powerOnLogicalServers operation on https\://tufnellpark\:51443/hpio/controller/soap/v2?wsdl. Note that the inputs to this flow which correspond to web service inputs are optional inputs.  This is due to the fact that web services definitions usually incorrectly indicate that too many inputs are required, and mirroring those settings in the flow would force you to enter unused values when running the flow.  The xmlTemplate input on the Invoke Method 2 step of this flow contains a template of the xml message to be sent, and the fields preceded by the comment "<\!--Optional\:-->" or "<\!--zero or more repetitions-->" are those which the web service indicates are optional; all others are indicated to be required.

Inputs\:
host - The host that is running the web service
port - The port on the host running the web service
logicalServerNames0 - The input named powerOnLogicalServers|0|logicalServerNames of the complex type\: powerOnLogicalServers|0
serviceName - The input named powerOnLogicalServers|serviceName of the complex type\: powerOnLogicalServers

Responses\:
success - The SOAP command was accepted by the web service
failure - Something went wrong while making the SOAP request

Extra Results\:
document - The raw XML response of the web service
documentStripped - The XML response of the web service stripped of namespaces
requestId - The output given by the XPath\: /Envelope/Body/powerOnLogicalServersResponse/requestId/text()

Create Application Tiers and deploy into ADM Input Parameters\: CPU_COUNT \: The CPU in number that the server should be set to. CSA_CONTEXT_ID \: CSA Context Id CSA_PROCESS_ID \: CSA Process Instance Id SVC_COMPONENT_ID \: This token will resolve to the Service component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:SVC_COMPONENT_ID] RSC_PROVIDER_ID \: This token will resolve to the Resource Provider Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:RSC_PROVIDER_ID] SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL \: This token will resolve to the subscriber’s email address. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL] RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID \: This token will resolve to the Resource Subscription Id that was created from the Resource Offering at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID] SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE \: This token will resolve to the Service component type. Eg\: Server.. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE] RSC_POOL_ID \: This token will resolve to the Resource pool Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_POOL_ID] SVC_INSTANCE_ID \: This token will resolve to the Service Instance Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_INSTANCE_ID] SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID \: This token will resolve to the Subscription Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID] PRN_COMPONENT_ID \: This token will resolve to the parent Component’s Service Component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: PRN_COMPONENT_ID] REQ_ORG_ID \: This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_ORG_ID] REQ_USER_ID \: This token will resolve to the User Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_USER_ID] USR_ORG_ID \: This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the subscriber. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: USR_ORG_ID] RSC_BINDING_ID \: This token will resolve to the Resource Binding Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_BINDING_ID] These tokens with the default values are resolved by CSA when the flow is invoked.
